properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 15 at 7:34AM CST until January 15 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...SNOW ACCUMULATIONS LIKELY ACROSS CENTRAL MINNESOTA AND LIGHT
ICING LIKELY OVER FAR SOUTHERN MINNESOTA TODAY...

.Snow will continue this morning across central Minnesota. Two to
four inches of total snow accumulation is expected for Douglas,
Todd, Morrison, Mille Lacs and Kanabec counties. Snow will
diminish this afternoon. In addition, freezing drizzle can be
expected this morning over far southern Minnesota, including the
Interstate 90 and Highway 14 and 60 corridors. A few hundredths
of an inch of ice accretion is expected along and south of a line
from Redwood Falls to Saint Peter to Faribault.

Motorists should exercise caution and allow extra time when
traveling this morning. Please drive slowly and with caution if
roads are slippery.

* WHAT...Snow. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHERE...Douglas, Morrison, Todd, Kanabec and Mille Lacs
Counties.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Motorists should exercise caution and allow
extra time when traveling. Please drive slowly and with caution
if roads are slippery.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
